                                                                         "0":  "{Champion}was caught in an upward patch trend. Pick rate and ban priority may start moving together."
                                                                     }
                                                     },
                                            "pc02":  {
                                                         "title":  {
                                                                       "0":  "{Champion} reacts to nerfs"
                                                                   },
                                                         "content":  {
                                                                         "0":  "A recent patch confirmed nerfs to{Champion}. If it was a core pick, backup options should not wait."
                                                                     }
                                                     },
                                            "pc03":  {
                                                         "title":  {
                                                                       "0":  "Rule patch key changes ({Count})"
                                                                   },
                                                         "content":  {
                                                                         "0":  "This patch changes{Count}match rules at once. Match length, objective value, and growth timing are baselines players have learned by feel, and all of them can shift together.\n\nIf you only separate out the numbers in the patch notes, the difference in how the game actually feels is hard to see. When the first objective's spawn timing, the value of midgame fights, and the timing of core item completions all move by a beat, the familiar calls and pathing have to be rebuilt together.\n\n In scrims, it is safer to replay similar pre- and post-patch situations under comparable conditions and check whether trades that clearly used to be profitable still remain profitable. In a period of major change, one or two comparison tests matter more than unverified instinct."
                                                                     }
                                                     },
                                            "pc04":  {
                                                         "title":  {
                                                                       "0":  "Economy patch reaction"
                                                                   },
                                                         "content":  {
                                                                         "0":  "This patch changes gold or eerience flow. Early fight rewards, lane-loss costs, and scaling-composition timing may all shift into a new pattern."
                                                                     }
                                                     },
                                            "pc05":  {
                                                         "title":  {
                                                                       "0":  "{Athlete} may benefit from the patch ({Champion})"
                                                                   },
                                                         "content":  {
                                                                         "0":  "{Athlete}'s main champion{Champion}received a buff. It is a card worth considering more actively in draft."
                                                                     }
                                                     }
                                        },
                               "league":  {
                                              "rk01":  {
                                                           "title":  {
                                                                         "0":  "{Team} leads the monthly table ({Rating})"
                                                                     },
                                                           "content":  {
                                                                           "0":  "{Team}has reached the top of the monthly ranking with rating{Rating}. Right now, this is the team the league is measuring itself against.{Team}"
                                                                       }
                                                       },
                                              "rk02":  {
                                                           "title":  {
                                                                         "0":  "{Team}'s rating is rising ({Delta})"
                                                                     },
                                                           "content":  {
                                                                           "0":  "{Team}'s recent rating movement is +{Delta}. Results are starting to change how the team is judged."
                                                                       }
                                                       },
                                              "rk04":  {
                                                           "title":  {
                                                                         "0":  "Monthly rank {Rank}... {Team} is now a name the league watches"
                                                                     },
                                                           "content":  {
                                                                           "0":  "From here, this is the stage where protecting the position may feel harder than reaching it.\n\nBreaking into the ranked tier means more than one result line: the team has started to draw the league's attention in earnest.\n\nWhat a rising team needs most is stability. After entering the upper ranks on one strong run, the net task is to prove through results that this run is not just a coincidence.\n\nOnce a team settles into the rankings, opposing clubs will also prepare with a clearly different intensity.{Rank}{Team}"
                                                                       }
                                                       },
                                              "rk05":  {
                                                           "title":  {
                                                                         "0":  "{Region} leads the regions ({Rating})"
                                                                     },
                                                           "content":  {
                                                                           "0":  "{Region}is rated near the top with rating{Rating}. International eectations are rising in the same momentum."
                                                                       }
                                                       },
                                              "rk06":  {
                                                           "title":  {
                                                                         "0":  "{Region} draws international expectations"
                                                                     },
                                                           "content":  {
                                                                           "0":  "{Region}has the highest international eectations right now. The region should define its style clearly before that pressure reaches the stage."
                                                                       }
                                                       },
                                              "rk07":  {
                                                           "title":  {
                                                                         "0":  "{Team} gives {Region} an underdog lift"
                                                                     },
                                                           "content":  {
                                                                           "0":  "{Team}'s win gave{Region}a small rebound signal. More repeated results are needed before the evaluation trend truly moves."
                                                                       }
                                                       },
                                              "rk08":  {
                                                           "title":  {
                                                                         "0":  "The top race is packed ({Diff})"
                                                                     },
                                                           "content":  {
                                                                           "0":  "Only{Diff}rating points separate the top five teams. One short winning or losing streak can reshape the standings quickly."
                                                                       }
                                                       }
                                          },
                               "season":  {
                                              "ss01":  {
                                                           "title":  {
                                                                         "0":  "{Team}'s season opener is close ({Days})"
                                                                     },
                                                           "content":  {
                                                                           "0":  "{Team}'s first league match is{Days}days away. This is the time to finalize starter condition and draft notes."
                                                                       }
                                                       },
                                              "ss02":  {
                                                           "title":  {
                                                                         "0":  "{Team} sits in the playoff fight ({Rank}, {Remaining})"
                                                                     },
                                                           "content":  {
                                                                           "0":  "{Team}is{Rank}with{Remaining}matches left. Each result can turn the season in a different direction, so the goal must be defined clearly."
                                                                       }
                                                       },
                                              "ss03":  {
                                                           "title":  {
                                                                         "0":  "{Team} nears early playoff safety ({Rank})"
                                                                     },
                                                           "content":  {
                                                                           "0":  "{Team}is currently ranked{Rank}, close to a stable playoff position. The remaining schedule is about protecting rank and managing condition."
                                                                       }
                                                       },
                                              "ss06":  {
                                                           "title":  {
                                                                         "0":  "{Team} stands on top of the season"
                                                                     },
                                                           "content":  {
                                                                           "0":  "{Team}finished the season on top. From here, fan eectations and core player values will be judged by a different standard."
                                                                       }
                                                       },
                                              "ss07":  {
                                                           "title":  {
                                                                         "0":  "{Team}'s runner-up finish lingers"
                                                                     },
                                                           "content":  {
                                                                           "0":  "{Team}stopped in the final, but proved its strength across the season. The disappointment is real, and so are the eectations for net season."
                                                                       }
                                                       },
                                              "ss08":  {
                                                           "title":  {
                                                                         "0":  "{Athlete}enters award talk ({Count})"
                                                                     },
                                                           "content":  {
                                                                           "0":  "{Athlete}has reached{Count}MVP awards and entered the award conversation. The attention around the player can move the club brand in a new pattern."
                                                                       }
                                                       },
                                              "ss09":  {
                                                           "title":  {
                                                                         "0":  "{League}'s fan pool grows"
                                                                     },
                                                           "content":  {
                                                                           "0":  "The end of{League}'s season has settled into a positive shape. Strong matches have helped widen the league's fan pool."
                                                                       }
                                                       },
                                              "ss10":  {
                                                           "title":  {
                                                                         "0":  "{League}'s fan pool slips"
                                                                     },
                                                           "content":  {
                                                                           "0":  "Fan reaction weakened late in the{League}season. Net season will need an early hook to pull attention back."
                                                                       }
                                                       }
                                          }
                           },
               "alert":  {
                             "player":  {
                                            "pl04":  {
                                                         "title":  {
                                                                       "0":  "{Athlete}'s stress warning is too loud to ignore"
                                                                   },
                                                         "content":  {
                                                                         "0":  "When training load, match pressure, and fan eectations all converge at once, the risk is not only on stage. The preparation before the match can start to shake first.\n\nA highly stressed player takes ordinary mistakes harder and reacts more sensitively to lineup competition or public response to recent matches. The first signs usually appear in decision speed, consistency of calls, and focus maintenance before they show up as raw performance loss.\n\n The staff should quickly check whether rest scheduling, reduced match frequency, or shorter streaming time is most closely tied to this stress. The larger the decision feels, the safer it is to change one thing at a time.{Athlete}{Stress}"
                                                                     }
                                                     },
                                            "pl03":  {
                                                         "title":  {
                                                                       "0":  "{Athlete}'s stamina is down to {Stamina}: time to act before the next run"
                                                                   },
                                                         "content":  {
                                                                         "0":  "If the net stretch of fitures is tight, this should be treated not as ordinary fatigue but as a warning that can turn directly into performance loss.\n\nA tired player may survive the first one or two sets, but as the match gets longer, reactions start to slip by a beat. Lane focus, rotation timing, and late-fight judgment all collect small delays, and those delays tend to surface all at once in decisive moments.\n\n If there is a viable substitute for the same slot, even one or two matches prioritized for recovery can make the late-season picture much steadier.{Athlete}{Stamina}"
                                                                     }
                                                     },
                                            "pl02":  {
                                                         "title":  {
                                                                       "0":  "{Athlete}'s condition has dropped to {Condition}: a warning before lineup decisions"
                                                                   },
                                                         "content":  {
                                                                         "0":  "This is a clear warning point; reputation or recent form alone is not enough reason to keep the name in the starting lineup unchanged.\n\nA player in poor condition can still follow the prepared plan, but the precision of the details usually dulls by a beat. Early lane phases and first skirmishes are where scenes that would normally be handled cleanly begin to look awkward.\n\n Rather than forcing a central role, it is often safer to review lower-pressure compositions and available substitute options at the same time.{Athlete}{Condition}"
                                                                     }
                                                     },
                                            "pl06":  {
                                                         "title":  {
                                                                       "0":  "{Athlete} is caught between attention and fatigue"
                                                                   },
                                                         "content":  {
                                                                         "0":  "As attention grows, the burden placed on a single player is growing heavier as well.\n\nFan interest is clearly an asset for the club, but if a tired player keeps being pushed to the front, that reaction can quickly shift into concern. Once performance decline appears in public even once or twice, the stardom built so far can come back as a reason for criticism.\n\n Rather than adding broadcasts or promotional work, restoring preparation time for the net match is the better way to keep fan eectations alive for longer.{Athlete}{Stamina}"
                                                                     }
                                                     },
                                            "pl10":  {
                                                         "title":  {
                                                                       "0":  "{Athlete}'s morale has fallen to {Morale}: waiting is risky"
                                                                   },
                                                         "content":  {
                                                                         "0":  "With signs of confidence slipping both in and out of matches, this is too heavy a stretch to simply wait out.\n\nA low-morale player can shrink after even a small mistake and often steps back inside internal competition. If benching, accumulated losses, and frustration over role all overlap, recovery tends to be far slower than usual.\n\n Instead of dragging the player straight back onto the biggest stage, it is usually safer to choose a matchup where a clean success eerience can be built.{Athlete}{Morale}"
                                                                     }
                                                     },
                                            "pl12":  {
                                                         "title":  {
                                                                       "0":  "{Athlete}'s contract is D-{Days}: there is little time left"
                                                                   },
                                                         "content":  {
                                                                         "0":  "If performance evaluation and renewal decisions are delayed any longer, the available options can start shrinking quickly.\n\nAs eiry approaches, the player's side and the club's side naturally begin to calculate differently. The player looks first at net season's role and the team's direction, while the club has to weigh cost pressure and replaceability at the same time.\n\n If the direction is to move on, the club still needs a clear line for how and until when the player will be used over the remaining schedule.{Athlete}{Days}"
                                                                     }
                                                     },
                                            "pl16":  {
                                                         "title":  {
                                                                       "0":  "{Athlete} sits on the bench as morale starts to wobble"
                                                                   },
                                                         "content":  {
                                                                         "0":  "This reads as more than ordinary substitute waiting; the player's response is clearly negative.\n\nWhen eclusion from the lineup repeats, a player starts questioning their place in the team itself. The more a player believes their performance has not been poor, the more frustration grows as bench time stretches.\n\n If starting immediately is difficult, the staff should at least be able to elain what conditions would open the net chance. That kind of clarity is what keeps the locker room stable.{Athlete}{Morale}"
                                                                     }
                                                     }
                                        },
                             "staff":  {
                                           "st01":  {
                                                        "title":  {
                                                                      "0":  "{Staff} staff contract expires in D-{Days}"
                                                                  },
                                                        "content":  {
                                                                        "0":  "{Staff}'s staff contract expires in D-{Days}.\nThe contract expires on <#fad33eff>{EndMonth} {EndDay}, {EndYear}<>. If the team plans to renew, check the terms before then.\nIf no renewal is completed, the staff member will become a free agent and leave the team."
                                                                    }
                                                    }
                                       },
                             "fan":  {
                                         "ff11":  {
                                                      "title":  {
                                                                    "0":  "{Team}'s losing streak cools the air outside the arena"
                                                                },
                                                      "content":  {
                                                                      "0":  "The fan response has moved beyond simple disappointment and is now asking what will actually change before the net match.\n\nWhen losses pile up, fans stop looking only at the final result. Draft direction, starting choices, and even post-match messages begin to draw suspicion. The longer the silence lasts, the heavier the frustration becomes inside it.\n\n Not a grand declaration or one dramatic decision, but visible proof in the match itself of what has changed and how. That is when aniety in the fanbase can start to settle.{Team}"
                                                                  }
                                                  },
                                         "ff06":  {
                                                      "title":  {
                                                                    "0":  "Fan satisfaction with {Team} has entered the danger zone"
                                                                },
                                                      "content":  {
                                                                      "0":  "Recent results and management choices have not given supporters enough confidence, and this is no longer a mood that can be brushed aside as a short-term swing.\n\nWhen satisfaction is low, even small decisions that would normally pass quietly start to look bigger. Lineup changes, transfer-market calls, and short messages after matches are all read more sharply than usual, so the same decision can receive a very different reaction.\n\n The atmosphere only starts to turn when improved match quality, clear reasons for selection, and the preparation direction for the net schedule show up in results, not just words.{Team}"
                                                                  }
                                                  },
                                         "pm08":  {
                                                      "title":  {
                                                                    "0":  "After the loss, {Team} needs change more than explanations"
                                                                },
                                                      "content":  {
                                                                      "0":  "The bigger issue is not just the result, but disappointment in how the defeat unfolded.\n\nFans can often accept a lost match, but a loss that looks underprepared tends to linger. Once the same problem repeats, distrust begins building before the net match even starts.\n\n At least one of draft direction, lineup decision, or match operation has to be clearly different in the result before the mood can start to recover.{Team}"
                                                                  }
                                                  },
                                         "ff02":  {
                                                      "title":  {
                                                                    "0":  "{Team}'s fan confidence is sliding fast"
                                                                },
                                                      "content":  {
                                                                      "0":  "This has moved beyond a simple slump in results and into a stage where the atmosphere around the whole club can be shaken.\n\nOnce fan trust falls sharply, even good news that follows often lands with less force than before. When trust is thin, small promotions or merchandise updates matter less than the problems that need to be solved inside the matches.\n\n Fan confidence starts rebuilding from the persuasiveness of one match. At this point, the net game is a faster answer than any announcement.{Team}"
                                                                  }
                                                  }
                                     },
                             "finance":  {
                                             "fi02":  {
                                                          "title":  {
                                                                        "0":  "{Team}, salary budget pressure ({Ratio})"
                                                                    },
                                                          "content":  {
                                                                          "0":  "With usage up to{Ratio}%, room for additional signings or renewal negotiations is narrowing quickly.\n\nSalary pressure is often felt more sharply after the early season than at the start. When poor condition or stamina issues create a need for replacements, a tight budget also reduces the tactical options the team can actually hold.\n\nEven with a cash balance of{Balance}, a rigid salary structure still limits mid-season decisions.  If every contract is carried with the same weight, the club may find itself unable to move when the transfer market is truly needed.{SalaryBudget}{SalaryUsage}{Team}"
                                                                      }
                                                      },
                                             "fi04":  {
                                                          "title":  {
                                                                        "0":  "{Team}, thin roster and limited budget ({Count})"
                                                                    },
                                                          "content":  {
                                                                          "0":  "This is a fragile structure where one player's condition problem can tighten the entire match-preparation plan.\n\nA thin roster may look manageable on quiet weeks, but its limit becomes clear when the schedule stacks up. Fatigue, poor condition, or draft matchup issues overlapping in the same week can narrow the preparation range for the net match immediately.\n\n If the team faces the remaining schedule without positional balance, it may be forced to abandon entire tactical options late in the season.{Count}{SalaryBudget}{Team}{TransferBudget}"
                                                                      }
                                                      }
                                         },
                             "transfer":  {
                                              "tf09":  {
                                                           "title":  {
                                                                         "0":  "{Athlete} player contract expires in D-{Days}"
                                                                     },
                                                           "content":  {
                                                                           "0":  "{Athlete}'s player contract expires in D-{Days}.\nThe contract expires on <#fad33eff>{EndMonth} {EndDay}, {EndYear}<>. If the team plans to renew, check the terms before then.\nIf no renewal is completed, the player will become a free agent and leave the team."
                                                                       }
                                                       },
                                              "tf08":  {
                                                           "title":  {
                                                                         "0":  "{Athlete} is tempting, but {Team} has to recheck the budget"
                                                                     },
                                                           "content":  {
                                                                           "0":  "{Team} is considering {Athlete}, but the transfer cost could strain the current budget.\nA high-price move can narrow later choices for renewals, backups, and mid-season adjustments.\nBefore pushing the negotiation further, compare the upgrade value against the room left in the squad plan."
                                                                       }
                                                       },
                                              "tf10":  {
                                                           "title":  {
                                                                         "0":  "{Team}'s {Position} depth needs attention"
                                                                     },
                                                           "content":  {
                                                                           "0":  "{Team}'s {Position} depth is thin.\nIf the schedule stacks up or a starter's condition drops, match preparation can tighten quickly.\nA realistic backup who can stabilize rotation may matter more than chasing a bigger name."
                                                                       }
                                                       }
                                          },
                             "pre_match":  {
                                               "pr07":  {
                                                            "title":  {
                                                                          "0":  "{Team}, pre-match stamina warning ({EnemyTeam})"
                                                                      },
                                                            "content":  {
                                                                            "0":  "In this matchup, endurance may become the problem before raw performance does.\n\nA tired team often looks shakier in the second and third sets than in the first. However precise the early plan may be, the longer the match runs, the more decision speed and call focus decline together.\n\n If the team drifts into a long match without a decision, it risks collapsing all at once in the later stage.{EnemyTeam}{Stamina}{Team}"
                                                                        }
                                                        },
                                               "pr09":  {
                                                            "title":  {
                                                                          "0":  "{EnemyTeam} head-to-head pressure ({Team})"
                                                                      },
                                                            "content":  {
                                                                            "0":  "This matchup requires not only tactical preparation, but also management of the psychological weight the players will carry.\n\nA poor head-to-head history can make decisions conservative before the match even begins. Skirmishes or draft choices that would normally be attempted lightly can start to feel like something that needs one more hesitation.\n\n Without a clear direction for the first draft phase and the first set, the team can start being pulled down by the weight of the matchup before play even settles.{EnemyTeam}{Team}"
                                                                        }
                                                        },
                                               "pr11":  {
                                                            "title":  {
                                                                          "0":  "{EnemyTeam} objective warning ({Team})"
                                                                      },
                                                            "content":  {
                                                                            "0":  "{EnemyTeam}has shown a clear strength around major objective timings.\n\nObjective fights are not decided by combat power alone. Vision control, rotation timing, and the timing of key skills need to line up before the result follows. Once the flow starts slipping, the net objective often begins from a worse position as well.\n\n Reducing scenes where the team gathers vaguely and only piles up losses may become the biggest variable in this match."
                                                                        }
                                                        }
                                           },
                             "training":  {
                                              "tr04":  {
                                                           "title":  {
                                                                         "0":  "{Athlete}, training decline detected ({Amount})"
                                                                     },
                                                           "content":  {
                                                                           "0":  "{Athlete}'s recent training report shows{Amount}stat drops. This is the point to determine whether it is just a condition wobble or whether the training direction itself is not suited to the player.\n\nOne training loss is not a major issue if it ends there, but repeated losses on the same player can derail the entire development plan. During the season, recovery and match readiness are tied together, so the approach has to be more careful than usual.\n\n Instead of pushing harder immediately, it is much safer to cut off the cause of the loss first.{Athlete}"
                                                                       }
                                                       }
                                          },
                             "scout":  {
                                           "sc08":  {
                                                        "title":  {
                                                                      "0":  "{Athlete} catches the eye, but the salary is heavy for {Team}"
                                                                  },
                                                        "content":  {
                                                                        "0":  "Signing a high-salary player is not just about filling one slot. Eisting renewal talks, backup reinforcement, and possible mid-season spending all start moving on the same graph.\n\n If that confidence is not there, using the same money to balance positions often creates a much larger effect.{Athlete}{Team}"
                                                                    }
                                                    },
                                           "sc09":  {
                                                        "title":  {
                                                                      "0":  "{Athlete}'s report is strong, but the fee puts {Team} at a crossroads"
                                                                  },
                                                        "content":  {
                                                                        "0":  "No matter how positive the scouting report looks, the biggest variable is whether the club can actually handle the negotiation cost.\n\nThe burden of a high-fee decision often returns more strongly after a successful signing than after a failed one. If the budget is concentrated on one player, the room to cover other weaknesses shrinks immediately.\n\n If the position is not truly necessary, stopping at the interest stage can be a perfectly reasonable decision.{Athlete}{Team}"
                                                                    }
                                                    }
                                       },
                             "league":  {
                                            "rk03":  {
                                                         "title":  {
                                                                       "0":  "{Team}, rating decline ({Delta})"
                                                                   },
                                                         "content":  {
                                                                         "0":  "The loss left on the standings is growing too heavy to dismiss as a short-term slump.\n\nA rating drop affects the way upcoming opponents look at the team. Even a side once treated as strong will face more aggressive pressure in draft and match operation if the decline lasts long enough.\n\n Rather than forcing a dramatic turnaround, one clean win built by reducing mistakes is the real first step toward rating recovery.{Delta}{Team}"
                                                                     }
                                                     }
                                        },
                             "season":  {
                                            "ss04":  {
                                                         "title":  {
                                                                       "0":  "{Team}, playoff race warning ({Rank}, {Remaining})"
                                                                   },
                                                         "content":  {
                                                                         "0":  "The chance is still alive, but one more slip can make the playoff math turn sharply against them.\n\nLate-season lower-table races are hard to read through win count alone. Head-to-head results, remaining schedule difficulty, and the form of rival teams all have to be seen together before the real position becomes clear. Miss even one must-win match from here and there may not be enough time to recover.\n\n Separating must-win matches from games where variables can be tested is much more realistic than preparing every match the same way.{Rank}{Remaining}{Team}"
                                                                     }
                                                     },
                                            "ss05":  {
                                                         "title":  {
                                                                       "0":  "{Team}, bottom-table warning ({Rank})"
                                                                   },
                                                         "content":  {
                                                                         "0":  "Spending too much time near the bottom of the standings can quickly pull both locker-room mood and fan response into a worse rhythm.\n\nA bottom-table fight is not just a performance issue. Once losses repeat, lineup decisions, recruitment calls, and training direction all start receiving a different kind of suspicion.\n\n Instead of talking about title contention, the first decision is to break one collapsing pattern in the net match. Only after that line is cut can the recovery graph start to appear again.{Rank}{Team}"
                                                                     }
                                                     }
                                        },
                             "meta":  {
                                          "pc06":  {
                                                       "title":  {
                                                                     "0":  "The patch blade is pointed at {Athlete}'s main card, {Champion}"
                                                                 },
                                                       "content":  {
                                                                       "0":  "This is a clear warning point where the familiar choice can no longer be trusted without checking the risk.\n\nPatch risk follows separately from the player's own skill. If the champion's power drops by one tier, the same level of mastery produces less impact in the match, and opposing teams can enter draft with easier calculations.\n\n The later that preparation comes, the faster the options available in draft will shrink.{Athlete}{Champion}{Champion}"
                                                                   }
                                                   }
                                      }
                         },
